               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Ammǝstu ʾaʿmāda mestir "The Five Pillars of Mystery" (fols.
                     2r-124v)&#xD; - Introduction (fols. 2r-5v)&#xD; - Mǝśṭira Śǝllāse
                     (fols.6r-20v)&#xD; - Mǝśṭira śǝggāwe (fols. 20v-50r)&#xD; - Mǝśṭira ṭǝmqat
                     (fols. 50r-78v)&#xD; - Mǝśṭira qʷǝrbān (fols. 78v-94v)&#xD; - Mǝśṭira tǝnśāʾe
                     mutān (fols. 94v-124v)&#xD; II) Tǝmhǝrta ḫǝbuʾāt "Teaching of Mysteries"
                     (125r-129r), here entitled as Tǝʾǝmǝrtä ḫǝbuʾāt (complete, cp. E.
                     HAMMERSCHMIDT, Äthiopische liturgische Texte der Bodleian Library in Oxford,
                     Berlin 1960 (Deutsche Akademie der Wissenschaften zu Berlin, Institut für
                     Orientforschung 38), 37-72).</summary>
